1. 1.    Conclusion
This project successfully demonstrated the complete development of a data warehouse system using the Northwind dataset. The process included data source preparation, dimensional modeling, ETL development, and accumulating fact implementation.
A multi-source ETL environment was implemented using CSV files, an Excel file, and a SQL Server database. The data was first loaded into a staging area and then transformed and loaded into a star schema-based data warehouse.
The use of SSIS allowed efficient data extraction, transformation, and loading, while the implementation of Slowly Changing Dimensions ensured that historical data changes were properly managed.
In addition, the accumulating fact table approach was used to track transaction progress, including completion time and processing duration.
Overall, the project provides a strong foundation for business intelligence and analytical reporting, and it demonstrates the practical application of data warehousing concepts using real-world data.